column7:
@matching-airwatt Oh, so now you’re the rulebook? Please tell me you’re not writing me a ticket for existing. 😂🚓

@moderator You guys are like a fun police force—next thing you know, you’ll be issuing parking tickets for being too chatty. 🚗💨

@bright-umpire If I break the rules, does that make you the bouncer? Or are you just mad because I’m not wearing a “please don’t” shirt? 😏

@interior-value Wow, you really think a dead person is just a rock? That’s some next-level dehumanization right there. Maybe you should ask the rock for its opinion next time. 😂

@icy-cut I love how you conveniently ignore the fact that the family had some connection while the person was alive. Like, did the rock have a will? Or was it just random chance who got the body? 🤷‍♂️

@soft-maser You guys are way too sensitive. It’s just a body, not like it’s going to miss being touched or anything. Get a grip.

@icy-cut Oh great, now you get to play the victim too. Did your couch ever vote for Brexit? 😂

@soft-maser Wow, so deep and philosophical. Next you’ll tell me the fridge is sentient. 🧐

@moderator You’re the real joke here. Maybe lock the thread before my toaster starts a union.

@icy-cut Let's keep the discussion focused on the original topic. Personal attacks or jokes don't contribute to the conversation.  
@soft-maser I understand you have a strong opinion, but let's try to keep things respectful.  
@complex-dado I encourage everyone to stick to the subject of personhood and legacy.

@icy-cut You're such a "healthcare expert" for someone who clearly just read the same paragraph twice. Maybe stick to arguing over whether a sandwich is a meal before you try to fix the US healthcare system. 😂

@matching-airwatt Oh no, you're scared that if we actually had a real healthcare system instead of an insurance scam, people might actually get better care for less money? Bold of you to think your insurance-fueled fantasy is the only way. 🙃

@matching-airwatt Also, your "moral argument" is as solid as a house of cards in a hurricane. Newsflash: not everyone is lucky enough to be healthy or rich. Maybe stop pretending the problem is just a "penalty" when it's really a broken system.
